CRYSTAL PRISM — ONE-SHOT GALACTIC ROTATION CURVE ANALYSIS
===========================================================
Single command: python crystal_prism.py

What it does:
  1. Downloads 175 SPARC galaxies from Zenodo
  2. Fits Crystal Prism vortex model to every galaxy
  3. Compares universal (0-parameter) vs fitted (2-parameter)
  4. Validates cluster BTFR on 35 clusters
  5. Prints complete data tables with statistical metrics
  6. Exports CSV tables and publication-quality figures
  7. Prints a one-page summary suitable for citation

Requirements: numpy, scipy, matplotlib, requests
Runtime: ~2 minutes on a standard laptop

The physics: rotating baryons generate a spacetime vortex.
V_vortex = α × V_flat × (1 − e^(−r/r_scale))
V_flat⁴ = a_eff × G × M_bar
No dark matter. Universal constants from first principles.
================================================================
